SELECT m.id, 'Meet the Team', 'meet-the-team', '<h2>Meet the Team</h2><h3>Kacy Orr, President</h3><figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Photo of Kacy Orr — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>Kacy, a forward-thinking visionary, plays a pivotal role in shaping the strategic direction of Innovative Air Technologies. While he actively oversees all facets of company operations, Kacy&apos;s primary areas of passion and expertise lie within the realms of sales and engineering. His main objective revolves around ensuring that IAT is equipped to offer customers the valuable resources required for resolving their humidity-related challenges, while also nurturing customer relationships that will endure for years to come.</p><p>Kacy&apos;s journey in the humidity control industry has deep roots. His extensive experience and affinity for desiccant dehumidification are found in his upbringing and professional history.</p><p>Before founding Innovative Air Technologies in 2001, Kacy dedicated his full-time efforts to Low Humidity Systems, a company owned by his father, Jerry, since 1981. Raised within the industry of desiccant dehumidification, Kacy brings a wealth of industry knowledge and a commitment to excellence that underscores his leadership within the organization.</p><p><strong>Stuff we leave out of the official bio:</strong></p><ul><li>He has 4 dogs.</li><li>He loves soccer &amp; golf.</li></ul><h3>Crystal Hill, Director of Operations</h3><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>Crystal has been an integral part of the Innovative Air Technologies team since its inception in 2001. Prior to joining IAT, she had the privilege of working alongside Jerry at Low Humidity Systems, further enriching her industry experience.</p><p>With over 20 years of combined expertise in customer service and comprehensive office functions, Crystal brings a wealth of knowledge and dedication to her role. She excels as a proficient multitasker, ensuring the successful execution of responsibilities. Crystal&apos;s unwavering commitment to excellence is evident in every aspect of her work.</p><p><strong>What&apos;s not in the official bio:</strong></p><p>Next to Kacy, Crystal is the knower of all the things.</p><h3>James Pope, Director of Engineering &amp; Production</h3><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>James, hailing from the East Coast of Canada, holds degrees in Civil Engineering from both New Brunswick Community College and Old Dominion University. James began his professional journey with a strong foundation in engineering principles. In 2010, he relocated to the United States alongside his family, marking a significant juncture in his career.</p><p>James&apos; fascination with engineering traces back to his formative years, where he enthusiastically engaged in electronic projects alongside his grandfather. This early exposure kindled a lifelong passion for design and innovation, a fervor that has only intensified over the course of his 20-year career in engineering.</p><p>James joined the Innovative Air Technologies team in 2015, assuming the role of Design Engineer. His exemplary dedication, proficiency, and unwavering commitment to excellence swiftly propelled him into the position of Engineering Manager.</p><p><strong>What the official bio didn&apos;t tell you:</strong></p><p>If you can&apos;t find him, he&apos;s probably in the breakroom making coffee.</p><h3>David Schurk, National Sales Manager</h3><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>David, holding credentials as DES, CEM, LEED-AP, COS, WEP 57, CIAQ, is National Sales Manager for Innovative Air Technologies in Covington, GA. He also serves as an ASHRAE Distinguished Lecturer and ASHRAE Life Member, and Committee Chair for the ASHRAE Sustainability and Decarbonization Leadership Task Force. He has over 40 years of experience in the design and analysis of heating, ventilating, and air-conditioning systems for a variety of market sectors, with special focus on healthcare and aerospace environmental control and air quality.</p><p><strong>You won&apos;t see this in the official bio:</strong></p><ul><li>He starts every morning (when at home) in a coffee shop — if he can find one open as early as he wakes up.</li><li>He loves spending time with his 5 grandchildren.</li></ul><h3>Jerry Orr, Humidity Consultant</h3><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>For those seeking a wealth of seasoned expertise, Jerry stands as an exemplary figure. With an unparalleled legacy spanning over five decades in the industry of desiccant dehumidification and humidity control, Jerry&apos;s unique career is a testament to his unwavering commitment to the field.</p><p>From 1951 to 2001, Jerry owned and operated Low Humidity Systems, a period during which he cemented his reputation as a pioneer and authority in the dehumidification industry. In 2001, he opted for semi-retirement, choosing to continue his journey by joining Innovative Air Technologies as an expert humidity consultant.</p><p>Jerry&apos;s exceptional career is complemented by his dedicated service to the United States Air Force from 1953 to 1963. His experience and enduring dedication are invaluable assets to Innovative Air Technologies, representing a legacy that continues to shape the humidity control industry to this day.</p><p><strong>Not in the bio:</strong></p><p>Jerry is the humidity Yoda. &ldquo;Always Other Possibilities.&rdquo;</p><h3>Summer Neal, Marketing Manager</h3><p><strong>The Official Bio:</strong></p><p>Summer Neal is a versatile professional with a diverse background spanning healthcare, marketing, and communications. After 22 years as a dental hygienist, Summer transitioned her career path to pursue her passion for marketing by obtaining a Bachelor of Science in Strategic Communications from Liberty University (2022).</p><p>In addition to her role as Marketing Manager at Innovative Air Technologies, Summer volunteers as Communications Director for her local church, and serves as the Social Media Manager for the Mayor of Porterdale, GA.</p><p><strong>What&apos;s not in the official bio:</strong></p><p>Coffee is her love language — she doesn&apos;t interact with people in the morning until after coffee. She also sings, plays piano, and loves Superman!</p>', 4, TRUE, 5
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'onboarding' AND m.slug = 'welcome-to-iat'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
